If you have special language, parsing, or scoring requirements for
your `string` data, you can apply the following options to your
index definition:**Analyzers-syntax:**Built-in AnalyzersTo specify how MongoDB Search breaks your text fields into tokens,
you can set [built-in analyzers](ref-built-in-analyzers) in your MongoDB Search index.```json
{
  "analyzer": "<index-analyzer-name>", // top-level index analyzer, used if no analyzer is set in the field mappings
  "searchAnalyzer": "<search-analyzer-name>", // query text analyzer, typically the same as the index analyzer
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": <boolean>,
    "fields":{
      "<field-name>": [
        {
          "type": "string|autocomplete",
          "analyzer": "<field-analyzer-name>" // field-specific index analyzer
          "multi": {
            "<multi-option-name>": {
              "type": "string|autocomplete",
              "analyzer": "<alternate-analyzer-name>" // multi-option specific index analyzer
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```**Custom-analyzers-syntax:**Custom AnalyzersTo customize how MongoDB Search breaks text into tokens, you can
define a [Custom analyzers](custom-analyzers) in the
`analyzers` field of your MongoDB Search index.```json
{
  "analyzers": [
    {
      "name": "<custom-analyzer-name>",
      "tokenizer": {
        "type": "<tokenizer-type>"
      }
    },
    ...
  ]
}
```**Synonyms-syntax:**SynonymsTo run queries with the [text](text-ref) operator that
account for terms with the same or similar meanings, you can
define [Synonym](synonyms-ref) in the `synonyms`
field of your MongoDB Search index.```json
{ 
  "synonyms": [
    {
      "name": "<synonym-mapping-name>",
      "source": {
        "collection": "<source-collection-name>"
      },
      "analyzer": "<synonym-mapping-analyzer>"
    }
  ] 
}

```**Scoring-syntax:**ScoringTo set which similarity algorithm MongoDB Search uses to calculate
relevance scores during queries, specify an algorithm in the
`similarity.type` property for your `string` fields
indexed as the MongoDB Search [string](bson-data-types-string)
or [tokenization](bson-data-types-autocomplete) type.This option determines how the [text](text-ref),
[Phrase](phrase-ref), [queryString](querystring-ref), and [autocomplete](more-like-this-ref) operators calculate relevance scores.
To learn more about the different similarity algorithms, see
[Score Details](fts-similarity-algorithms).```json
  "mappings": {
    "fields": {
      "<field-name>": {
        "type": "string|autocomplete",
        "similarity": {
          "type": "bm25|boolean|stableTfl"
        },
      },
      "<field-name>": {
        "type": "string",
        "multi": {
          "<multi-option-name>": {
            "type": "string",
            "similarity": {
              "type": "bm25|boolean|stableTfl"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }

```

